Inside Partition (Ordering)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Partition-0
   Offset 0  →  "Order #101 Created"
   Offset 1  →  "Order #101 Payment Done"
   Offset 2  →  "Order #101 Packed"
   Offset 3  →  "Order #101 Shipped"

👉 Offset sequence = Ordering guarantee
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────




OFFSET ही Kafka ka message ordering hota hai.
Ordering = Offset ka sequence.
Offset decide karta hai ki message kis order me likha aur padha jayega.

Kafka partition ke andar:
Har message ko ek unique offset number milta hai
Ye offset 0, 1, 2, 3… aise sequence me hota hai
Ye sequence hi message ka order hota hai

Partition-0:
Offset 0 → "Order Created"
Offset 1 → "Payment Done"
Offset 2 → "Order Shipped"


Why offset = ordering?
Because Kafka har partition ke andar messages ko sequential index deta hai:
Producer ka message → partition me append hota hai
Append ka order hi offset ka order hota hai
Consumer exactly offset ke order me hi read karta hai


Below is **SUPER SIMPLE Kafka ordering code** —
Exactly woh 2 lines jisse **ordering ensure hoti hai** 👇

